{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-2395"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of articles of concrete, cement and plaster"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "2395"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :concrete-cement-plaster-products/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :materials-safety :resource-efficiency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :concrete-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "ConcreteAdvisor ⊣ Concrete Plant Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION
 actor for concrete/cement/plaster-products plants (mixing/batching ->
 molding/casting -> curing production lines for precast panels, pipes,
 blocks, paving slabs and plasterboard) -- not direct mixing/molding-
 line-equipment control authority. Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Eleven concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct mixing/molding-line-equipment control), permanent
 mixing-line-actuate block, independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-weight recompute against the batch's own logged
 weight, double-schedule guard, product-type validation, dimensional-
 deviation plausibility validation, and defect-rate plausibility
 validation. Materials-safety/equipment-safety concern flagging
 (silica dust, curing-heat) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant
 supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to
 auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
